reviews.text: It's a very nice little station on the Scenic Medway Valley Line with a nice country feel to it, especially with the river directly next to it, and the station itself is nice and clean, and has quite a peaceful air to it. However, there is no step-free access from the station entrance to the platform for customers requiring or getting off of Tonbridge-bound services. Other than that, a really nice station to use!
An attractive historic railway station on the scenic Medway Valley Line.
